  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2005",
  "title": "connectToggle doesn't work",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\nCurrent toggle always passes the value to algolia as undefined:\r\n\r\nWhen clicking a toggle, it adds this to the search state: `?toggle%5Bremote%5D=true`.\r\nInspecting the algolia request sends remote: undefined:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"804\" alt=\"screen shot 2017-02-23 at 9 39 40 am\" src=\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/449136/23263371/0c8a826c-f9ac-11e6-9ac1-c6ff8c307779.png\">\r\n\r\nEven using refine(true) in component did mount will do the exact same thing, it updates the search state, but passes undefined.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\nFor the toggle to send the value I pass in createURL / refine to actually be used.\r\n\r\n**What project are you opening an issue for?**\r\n- react-instantsearch 3.2\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\n\r\n3.2",
